**CFI Supabase**

**Complete Upload & Management Guide**

*Circular Fertiliser Industries \| Bogor, West Java \| March 2026*

*v1.0 --- Beginner Edition*

**1. What is Supabase and How CFI Uses It**

Supabase is your live database. Think of it as a very smart Excel
spreadsheet that lives on the internet, that your React dashboard
(Lovable) reads from. Every number, organism name, chemical dose, and
lab value that appears on your dashboard can come from Supabase instead
of being hardcoded.

The CFI Supabase database has 11 core tables:

  ------------------------ ------------------------------------- ---------
  **Table Name**           **What It Stores**                    **\#
                                                                 Rows**

  cfi_feedstock_values     Lab values for EFB, OPDC, POME sludge \~31

  cfi_chemical_library     20 chemicals --- prices, doses, RSPO  20
                           status                                

  cfi_biological_library   43 organisms --- BSF safety, conflict 43
                           lists                                 

  cfi_pricing              Urea, TSP, MOP, BSF product prices    \~15

  cfi_guardrails           Locked constants --- CLASS A cannot   \~25
                           be changed                            

  cfi_lab_results          New lab uploads with delta flags      Grows
                                                                 over time

  cfi_data_gaps            Confirmed missing data (e.g. POME     \~10
                           C:N)                                  

  cfi_conflict_log         Rejected values --- IMMUTABLE         Grows
                                                                 over time

  cfi_soil_profiles        5 Indonesian palm soil types          5

  cfi_change_log           Every single data change ---          Grows
                           IMMUTABLE                             over time

  cfi_solutions            Data lake from AI research runs       Grows
                                                                 over time
  ------------------------ ------------------------------------- ---------

> *RULE: Supabase is append-only. You NEVER delete rows. You soft-delete
> using is_active = false. The change_log and conflict_log can NEVER be
> deleted.*

